seriesStmt.title: Gregor Joseph Werner: A thematic catalogue of his works

physMedium.p: Source consists of four parts (vl 1, vl 2, vlc, b), of which the b part is bound, and the remaining parts are secured between the back flyleaf and pastedown by a linen band. In quarter-binding (black linen, black marbled paper) with front and end flyleaves. Same copyist throughout.

annot.p:
Violino 1
2 nested bifolios; 29.3x20.4 cm.
Title page: Violino Primo | [two stamps]
In 2o; upright format; title page (fol. 1r), music (fols. 1v–4v). Hand-ruled paper, 10 staves (12 mm) in light brown ink and music in black ink; bottom two staves on fol. 2r, bottom three staves on fol. 3r, and bottom five staves on fol. 4v have not been used. A clean copy without corrections; folio number “5” has been added at the top right corner of fol. 1r. Paper of a fairly dense quality.

Violino 2
2 nested bifolios; 29.3x20.4 cm.
Title page: Violino Secondo
In 2o; upright format; title page (fol. 1r), music (fols. 1v–4v). Hand-ruled paper, 10 staves (12 mm) in light brown ink and music in black ink; bottom staff on fol. 1v, bottom six staves on fol. 3r, bottom two staves in fol. 4r, and bottom five staves on fol. 4v have not been used. A clean copy without corrections; folio numbers “9” and “10” have been added at the top right corner of fol. 1r and 2r, respectively. Paper of a fairly dense quality.

Violoncello
2 nested bifolios; 29.3x20.4 cm.
Title page: Violoncello Solo
In 2o; upright format; title page (fol. 1r), music (fols. 1v–4v). Hand-ruled paper, 10 staves (12 mm) in light brown ink and music in black ink; bottom staff on fol. 2r, bottom two staves on fol. 4r, and bottom six staves on fol. 4v have not been used. A clean copy without corrections; folio numbers “13” and “16” have been added at the top right corner of fol. 1r and 4r, respectively. Paper of a fairly dense quality.

Basso
2 nested bifolios; 29.3x20.4 cm.
Title page: Concerto per la Camera | à 4 [in pencil: (in A] | 2 Violini | Violoncello Concer: | Con | Baſso | Del Sigre Werner | [two stamps]. At top left corner: “S.m. 3751” in black ink; at top right corner: “9.” in blue pencil.
In 2o; upright format; title page (fol. 1r), music (fols. 1v–4r), blank page (fol. 4v). Hand-ruled paper, 10 staves (12 mm) in light brown ink and music in black ink; bottom two staves on fol. 4v have not been used. A clean copy without corrections; folio numbers “1”, “2”, and “4” have been added at the top right corner of fol. 1r, 2r, and 4r, respectively. Paper of a fairly dense quality.
